result.execSummary:
The defendant Cordelia N Guerrero was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 1:10 p.m. Defendant Cordelia N Guerrero in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant failed to appear in court on March 9, 2015. The defendant wishes to enter a plea today. Defendant waives her right to be personally present in the courtroom.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Ct 1 - NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Ct 2 - DRI. No statement by DE. Court orders: 4 days WCJ - GT, 3 days CFTS - Time served sentence, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. Appeal rights given. Bond previously posted has been forfeited. Motion by Atty Szilagyi for expungment upon full payment of the costs. The court declines to grant the opportunity for expungment.

Case called @ 3:23 p.m. Defendant Cordelia N Guerrero not in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Based on non appearance the Court authorizes the issuance of a bench warrant extraditable within the State of Wisconsin. 15TR150 - Default Judgment entered. Court orders forfeiture noted on the citation w/ 60 DTP or PP.
Status conference on March 9, 2015 at 02:20 pm.
No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.

Case called @ 3:30 p.m. Defendant Cordelia N Guerrero in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant wishes to have counsel but cannot afford one at this time. Referred to SPD.   NGP entered on all matters.  Court order $250 Cash Bond. STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Status conference scheduled for March 9, 2015 at 02:20 pm.
